WEBVTT

23:59:37.970 --> 23:59:44.070
♫ We... are the crystal gems,
we'll always save the day, ♫

23:59:44.260 --> 23:59:49.000
♫ And if you think we can't,
we'll always find a way, ♫

23:59:49.360 --> 23:59:54.410
♫ That's why the people
of this world believe in, ♫

23:59:54.830 --> 23:59:59.960
♫ Garnet, Amethyst, and
Pearl... and Steven ♫

00:00.180 --> 00:01.680
Episode 1b
"Laser Light Cannon"

00:05.910 --> 00:08.220
Hey, Fryman, give me the bits!

00:08.650 --> 00:10.280
Steven, we're closed!

00:10.690 --> 00:12.080
Ohh, what...

00:12.600 --> 00:16.070
Give him the bits!
The bits! The bits!

00:16.260 --> 00:19.700
The bits! The bits! The bits!

00:19.780 --> 00:22.500
Okay, okay. Take it easy
on the counter, will ya?

00:23.080 --> 00:24.220
Yes!

00:27.520 --> 00:29.600
I can give you actual
fries, if you want.

00:30.170 --> 00:31.420
Just the bits, please.

00:32.200 --> 00:32.810
Thanks!

00:35.340 --> 00:38.100
Ahh, sunset - my favorite time of day.

00:38.670 --> 00:43.380
The sun goes down, and the second
sun gets bigger and bigger in the sky.

00:45.340 --> 00:48.170
Yeah, that big, hot second suuu...

00:49.450 --> 00:51.620
Oh, no, what is that doing here?

00:52.960 --> 00:53.590
What is it?

00:53.840 --> 00:55.360
Aah! My bits!

00:56.750 --> 00:57.820
This is bad.

00:58.370 --> 00:59.820
Look at the size of it!

01:00.190 --> 01:02.280
I had no idea these things were so big!

01:02.290 --> 01:03.850
Garnet! Pearl!

01:04.819 --> 01:05.640
We saw!

01:05.840 --> 01:08.470
Some of us are trying
to protect humanity!

01:08.750 --> 01:09.760
Where were you?

01:11.030 --> 01:11.900
Eating fry bits.

01:12.350 --> 01:12.940
Ugh.

01:13.470 --> 01:14.130
Can I see?

01:15.140 --> 01:16.440
Whoa.

01:18.960 --> 01:20.540
It's a giant eyeball!

01:20.770 --> 01:21.870
Awesome!

01:21.930 --> 01:24.870
Not awesome, it a red eye!

01:25.110 --> 01:28.010
A red eye?
It's going to infect us all!

01:28.090 --> 01:29.500
That's pinkeye, Steven.

01:30.660 --> 01:32.610
It's going to crash into Beach City,

01:32.710 --> 01:36.630
and crush us, along with a bunch
of oblivious, innocent people!

01:36.700 --> 01:38.190
We have to stop it!

01:38.330 --> 01:39.720
What are we going to do?

01:40.110 --> 01:42.920
The only thing powerful enough
to destroy it is a light cannon,

01:42.920 --> 01:44.460
that belonged to Rose Quartz.

01:44.680 --> 01:45.310
My mom?

01:45.320 --> 01:48.260
If Rose were here,
this would be so easy.

01:48.600 --> 01:51.880
I know, but she is not,
and the cannon is missing.

01:52.200 --> 01:53.900
We'll have to find another solution.

01:54.090 --> 01:56.980
If it belonged to my mom, I
bet my dad knows where it is.

01:57.090 --> 02:00.620
He can help us save the day!
Huh?! Eh?!

02:01.450 --> 02:04.410
Greg is... nice, Steven.

02:04.910 --> 02:08.979
But I doubt Rose would entrust someone
like <i>him</i> with such a powerful weapon.

02:09.190 --> 02:10.800
Your dad is kind of a mess, Steven.

02:10.960 --> 02:11.910
Amethyst!

02:12.070 --> 02:13.300
I'm just saying!

02:13.420 --> 02:15.290
Even if she <i>did</i> leave it with him,

02:15.290 --> 02:19.230
he probably broke it, or lost it,
or dropped it in the ocean by now.

02:19.710 --> 02:20.420
True...

02:20.740 --> 02:23.650
No way! I'm sure he is just
keeping it somewhere safe.

02:23.880 --> 02:24.800
I'll go ask him.

02:25.200 --> 02:26.700
We can handle this, Steven.

02:27.290 --> 02:27.770
Ready?

02:29.000 --> 02:35.074
