02:37.130 --> 02:38.880
Uh, I'm gonna go.

02:39.280 --> 02:40.640
Okay, good luck.

02:42.480 --> 02:44.800
Dad, it's me!
Daaad?

02:45.470 --> 02:46.470
Are you in there?

02:47.220 --> 02:48.630
Wake... up!

02:48.890 --> 02:50.610
We have to save the world!

02:53.600 --> 02:54.510
Dad!

03:01.790 --> 03:03.780
Who's there? I have a waffle iron!

03:04.350 --> 03:05.200
Dad, it's me!

03:10.010 --> 03:10.750
Steven?

03:14.150 --> 03:15.740
I almost waffled your face!

03:15.950 --> 03:17.480
What are you doing up so late?

03:17.480 --> 03:20.560
What do you mean? The sun
just went down an hour ago.

03:22.510 --> 03:24.850
It was a slow day at the car wash.

03:25.100 --> 03:26.010
Anyway, what's up?

03:26.350 --> 03:30.170
Just needed to see your old man, pal
around, learn some lessons about life?

03:30.480 --> 03:31.160
No!

03:31.310 --> 03:34.420
I need the light cannon that belonged
to mom to blow up that eyeball!

03:34.710 --> 03:35.600
Eyeball?

03:35.760 --> 03:36.430
That!

03:43.430 --> 03:45.310
Wait. Is that a magical thing?

03:45.380 --> 03:47.790
The gems told me not to
get involved with magic stuff.

03:48.050 --> 03:51.080
I-it could be dangerous or interfere
with what's left of my hair.

03:51.320 --> 03:54.100
But they need mom's cannon.
You've got to know where it is!

03:54.270 --> 03:59.070
Like a cave dungeon or a cloud fortress
or in a clam at the bottom of the ocean.

03:59.680 --> 04:03.540
Well, I don't know about all that,
but I have an idea where it might be.

04:05.110 --> 04:06.950
A magical storage unit!

04:08.300 --> 04:11.430
Not exactly. But some would
say there's magic inside.

04:13.920 --> 04:16.970
It's just a shed I use to keep
things that don't fit in the van.

04:17.360 --> 04:20.480
If it's anywhere... it'll be in here.

04:27.640 --> 04:30.270
If I'm going in there,
I'm gonna need some gear.

04:34.540 --> 04:35.480
Here I go!

04:35.610 --> 04:36.280
Good luck!

04:38.730 --> 04:40.080
Whoa!

04:40.760 --> 04:42.100
Cool!

04:42.460 --> 04:44.120
It's like a dad museum!

04:51.150 --> 04:52.210
There it is!

04:56.830 --> 04:58.060
Do you golf?

04:58.270 --> 05:02.930
Ah, I like to think of myself as
someone who would golf... eventually.

05:04.330 --> 05:05.200
Yes!

05:06.920 --> 05:07.590
A drum.

05:13.880 --> 05:14.640
No.

05:14.720 --> 05:15.280
No.

05:16.140 --> 05:18.000
Oh, my gosh! Oh, my gosh! Oh, my gosh!

05:18.060 --> 05:18.880
Is this...?

05:23.030 --> 05:25.090
"Buy t-shirt cannons"?

05:27.220 --> 05:29.840
Hey, there's a bunch
of copies of your old CD!

05:30.930 --> 05:33.800
Oh, man.
I couldn't give those things away.

05:34.610 --> 05:36.420
You know, before I ran the car wash,

05:36.420 --> 05:39.360
when I was a one-man band,
I travelled the whole country.

05:39.660 --> 05:41.060
I know, dad.

05:41.300 --> 05:44.870
When I came to play a concert here in
Beach City, no one showed up except...

05:44.930 --> 05:46.260
An alligator!

05:46.450 --> 05:47.730
No, it was your mother.

05:48.530 --> 05:49.370
I know.

05:49.630 --> 05:51.510
And we were always
together after that,

05:51.860 --> 05:54.560
until she gave up her physical
form to bring you into the world.

05:55.090 --> 05:59.110
I don't know what a magic lady like her
ever saw in a plain old dope like me.

06:00.340 --> 06:01.370
Uh, dad?

06:01.670 --> 06:03.000
I broke a photo.

06:03.090 --> 06:03.980
It's okay, buddy.

06:04.490 --> 06:07.400
If every pork chop were perfect,
we wouldn't have hot dogs.

06:10.640 --> 06:11.510
The light cannon!

06:12.470 --> 06:14.850
Oh, boy. That thing's
giving me the willies.

06:15.100 --> 06:16.200
Dad, I found it!

06:16.730 --> 06:17.400
Really?

06:19.430 --> 06:20.360
Get the van!

06:32.510 --> 06:34.050
This thing could save the city!

06:34.140 --> 06:35.760
We've got to get it to the beach!

06:36.040 --> 06:38.290
How? It's too big for the van.

06:56.080 --> 06:57.360
Is it gonna be okay?

06:59.900 --> 07:01.850
If every pork chop were perfect...

07:01.880 --> 07:03.880
we wouldn't have hot dogs!

07:05.070 --> 07:07.970
That thing's getting huge!
It's freaking me out!

07:08.410 --> 07:10.180
Can't the van go any faster?

07:11.270 --> 07:12.570
This <i>is</i> faster!

07:13.030 --> 07:15.800
Don't worry. Come on.
Let's put on your CD.

07:17.210 --> 07:19.810
Huh, really? Uh,
come on, you've heard it.

07:20.380 --> 07:21.510
You come on.

07:26.040 --> 07:30.730
♫ I know I'm not that tall
I know I'm not that smart ♫

07:31.260 --> 07:34.430
♫ But-- let me drive my
Van into your heart  ♫

07:34.440 --> 07:37.590
♫ Let me drive my
Van into your heart ♫

07:37.590 --> 07:42.450
♫ I know I'm not that rich
I'm trying to get my start ♫

07:42.760 --> 07:46.120
♫ So, let me drive my
Van into your heart ♫

07:46.120 --> 07:48.930
♫ Let me drive my
Van into your heart ♫

07:49.380 --> 07:54.470
♫ And if we look out of place
Well, baby, that's okay ♫

07:54.550 --> 07:57.240
♫ I'll drive us into outer space ♫

07:58.270 --> 08:00.700
Throw me again.
I think I'm cracking it.

08:01.590 --> 08:02.620
Is that?

08:02.620 --> 08:03.290
Hey, guys!

08:05.500 --> 08:07.110
He really had it.

08:07.430 --> 08:08.920
We're saved!

08:09.780 --> 08:12.140
♫ Let me drive my
Van into your heart ♫

08:12.320 --> 08:14.970
♫ Let me drive my
Van into your heart ♫

08:15.230 --> 08:17.040
♫ Let me drive my
Van into your heart ♫

08:17.040 --> 08:18.740
Whoa! Whoa! Whoa!

08:19.230 --> 08:20.800
♫ ...van into your heart ♫

08:21.180 --> 08:23.620
♫ Let me drive my
Van into your heart ♫

08:23.620 --> 08:24.900
We have to use it now.

08:26.610 --> 08:29.080
I don't know how it works!
It was Rose's!

08:29.700 --> 08:31.060
Dad, how do we use it?

08:33.340 --> 08:35.340
Steven, this is serious.

08:35.860 --> 08:38.929
The gem. You have Rose's gem!

08:39.780 --> 08:40.490
That's it!

08:44.470 --> 08:45.680
Ugh! Come on!

08:45.710 --> 08:46.500
Stop that!

08:46.840 --> 08:48.090
It's no use!

08:48.200 --> 08:50.690
Fine! Forget it!
Throw me again!

08:50.890 --> 08:52.200
That's not going to work!

08:53.520 --> 08:56.890
I got this!
No! Wait! No, maybe I don't!

08:58.880 --> 09:03.230
Please, work. Unlock.
Activate. Go. Please?

09:03.900 --> 09:06.520
Everyone's counting on you!
You can't just be useless!

09:06.580 --> 09:07.730
I know you can help!

09:08.030 --> 09:12.550
It's okay, Steven! We'll figure out
something else! Something even better!

09:13.130 --> 09:17.740
R-right! If every pork chop were
perfect, we wouldn't have hot dogs!

09:27.250 --> 09:28.160
It's working!

09:37.420 --> 09:37.950
Steven!

09:38.440 --> 09:39.270
This is it.

09:39.440 --> 09:41.060
Brace yourselves!

10:10.550 --> 10:13.580
Steven, you just saved
most of Beach City!

10:14.180 --> 10:15.920
Sorry about that!

10:17.480 --> 10:18.080
What?

10:19.100 --> 10:20.730
How did you get it to work?

10:21.070 --> 10:23.340
I just said that thing
that dad always says.

10:23.830 --> 10:25.290
That thing about pork rinds?

10:25.850 --> 10:26.630
Hot dogs.

10:27.380 --> 10:28.030
Rose.

10:36.900 --> 10:37.980
My van!

10:38.310 --> 10:39.510
It's okay, dad.

10:39.870 --> 10:41.570
If every pork chop were perfect...

10:41.570 --> 10:42.930
I live in there!

10:43.670 --> 10:44.570
Wait up!

